:9:    \"description\" : \"This artifact provides Java utility APIs used by bnd, including class-file parsing, functional exception wrappers, memoization, result types, signatures, stream helpers, and immutable collection helpers. It is a compile-time support library for bnd and OSGi tooling, packaging reusable utilities that other bnd components can statically link or consume on the JVM.\",\nmetadata/org.ccil.cowan.tagsoup/tagsoup/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/ccil/cowan/tagsoup/tagsoup/$version$/tagsoup-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.ccil.cowan.tagsoup/tagsoup/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"N/A\",\nmetadata/org.ccil.cowan.tagsoup/tagsoup/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"N/A\",\nmetadata/org.ccil.cowan.tagsoup/tagsoup/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/ccil/cowan/tagsoup/tagsoup/$version$/tagsoup-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.ccil.cowan.tagsoup/tagsoup/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"TagSoup is a SAX-compliant Java parser for handling malformed real-world HTML through standard XML processing APIs. It also includes a command-line processor that can turn HTML input into clean HTML or well-formed XML approximating XHTML.\",\nmetadata/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/biz/aQute/bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/$version$/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/bndtools/bnd\",\nmetadata/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/bndtools/bnd/tree/$version$/biz.aQute.bndlib.tests/test/test\",\nmetadata/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/biz/aQute/bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/$version$/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"The biz.aQute.bnd.annotation artifact provides bnd-specific Java annotations for OSGi bundle metadata, package versioning, capabilities, service metadata, JPMS hints, licenses, and plugin declarations. These annotations are consumed by bnd and related tooling to generate or validate bundle headers and metadata without hard-coding that information in build instructions.\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/$version$/bcpkix-jdk15to18-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java/tree/r1rv77/pkix/src/test\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/$version$/bcpkix-jdk15to18-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Provides Bouncy Castle Java APIs for PKIX, CMS, PKCS, EAC, TSP, CMP, CRMF, OCSP, and certificate generation. It targets JDK 1.5 through JDK 1.8 and is typically used alongside a JCE/JCA provider such as Bouncy Castle's cryptography provider.\",\nmetadata/com.github.ajalt.clikt/clikt-core-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/github/ajalt/clikt/clikt-core-jvm/$version$/clikt-core-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/com.github.ajalt.clikt/clikt-core-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/ajalt/clikt\",\nmetadata/com.github.ajalt.clikt/clikt-core-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/ajalt/clikt/tree/$version$/test/src\",\nmetadata/com.github.ajalt.clikt/clikt-core-jvm/index.json